  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_radiotherapy_anatomical_treatment_site__opcs_">RADIOTHERAPY ANATOMICAL TREATMENT SITE (OPCS)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_classification_code">CLINICAL CLASSIFICATION CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_radiotherapy_anatomical_treatment_site__opcs_">RADIOTHERAPY ANATOMICAL TREATMENT SITE (OPCS)</xref>
 is the part of the body to which the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_radiotherapy_actual_dose">RADIOTHERAPY ACTUAL DOSE</xref>
 is administered.  </p>
  <p>
For the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_radiotherapy_data_set">Radiotherapy Data Set</xref>
, see the Radiotherapy Data Set Manual at: 
    <xref href="http://www.ncin.org.uk/collecting_and_using_data/rtds"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National Radiotherapy Data Set (RTDS)</xref>
, for the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS_Classification_of_Interventions_and_Procedures</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
) code to be used.  </p>


